author: Naomi Powell
title: ‘Unlike anything we’ve seen before’: Coronavirus lockdowns strain critical supply-chains in Canada
description: Grounded planes, shuttered warehouses and panic buying have created a perfect storm of obstacles to moving essential goods
content:
Canadian freight carriers are battling unprecedented challenges to deliver goods by land, air and ocean as sweeping travel restrictions, lockdowns and surges in demand strain critical links in global and domestic supply chains.
